1 AN ACT
2 To enact R.S. 40:1132, relative to ambulance providers; to provide for definitions; to
3 provide for Medicaid coverage of certain services; to provide for reimbursement
4 rates; to provide for rulemaking; and to provide for related matters.
5 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
6 Section 1. R.S. 40:1132 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
7 §1132. Ambulance provider treatment-in-place services; medical assistance
8 program
9 A. As used in this Section, the following definitions apply unless
10 otherwise indicated:
11 (1) "911 call" means a communication made on behalf of a beneficiary
12 indicating that the beneficiary may need emergency medical services.
13 (2) "Ambulance provider" means an ambulance provider as defined in
14 R.S. 40:1131. For purposes of this Section, "ambulance provider" does not
15 include an air ambulance provider.
16 (3) "Beneficiary" means a person who is entitled to receive covered
17 healthcare services under the terms of the medical assistance program.
18 (4) "Medical assistance program" means the medical assistance program
19 provided for in Title XIX of the Social Security Act as administered by the
20 Louisiana Department of Health.
21 (5) "Qualified medical practitioner" means a licensed physician, nurse
22 practitioner, or physician's assistant.
23 (6) "Treatment-in-place service" means an encounter between an
24 ambulance provider and beneficiary which takes place in response to a 911 call
25 where an assessment or treatment is provided by the ambulance provider to the
26 beneficiary but transport of the beneficiary is not performed.
27 B. Treatment-in-place services, as provided for by this Section, shall be
