1 a covered service under the medical assistance program.
2 C. Initiation and facilitation of treatment-in-place services may be
3 performed by ambulance providers on site to beneficiaries, with no transport,
4 and may include the use of audio and video telecommunication systems that
5 permit real-time communication between the ambulance provider and a
6 qualified medical practitioner. However, audio and video telecommunications
7 between the ambulance provider and a qualified medical practitioner shall not
8 be required in order for the ambulance provider to be reimbursed for
9 treatment-in-place services by the medical assistance program.
10 D. Treatment-in-place services shall only be provided in accordance with
11 the ambulance provider's medical direction and established protocols. Any
12 medical assessment or services rendered by EMS practitioners shall be
13 consistent with the practitioner's scope of practice.
14 E. All treatment-in-place services provided by ambulance providers
15 during the initiation and facilitation of the treatment-in-place encounter shall
16 be covered at the associated basic life support, emergency base rate, or the
17 advanced life support, Level 1 emergency base rate provided for in the
18 Medicaid fee schedule, depending on level of response and services rendered.
19 F. The Louisiana Department of Health shall promulgate rules and
20 regulations as necessary for the implementation of the provisions of this Section.
